                  <summary change="#add-summary">
                     1 copy of Zubdat al-nasab by Muḥammad Qāsim b. Ḥusain al-Nassābah, al-Ḥasanī al-Mukhtār al-ʻAbīdilī al-Ḥusainī al-Mūsavī al-Raz̤avī
                  </summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_4619-item1">
                     <author key="person_f2608">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied">Muḥammad Qāsim b. Ḥusain al-Nassābah, al-Ḥasanī al-Mukhtār al-ʻAbīdilī al-Ḥusainī al-Mūsavī al-Raz̤avī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">محمد قاسم بن حسین النسابه، الحسنی المختار العبیدلی الحسینی الموسوی الرضوی</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_8378">Zubdat al-nasab</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_8378">زبدة النسب</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="fa">انسب کلامی که از شهام روایح آن دماغ جان عالی نسبان صوامع قدس معٌطر گردد . . . اما بعد چون معرفت انسب عبوجب حدیث و کتاب امری مهم است الخ</incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="ar" defective="true"/>
                     <note>A short work, consisting of a muqaddimah, five fuṣūl, and a Khātimah, setting forth the names of the descendants of ʻAlī and the twelve Imāms, followed by the genealogy of <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="alt" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/3785262" key="viaf_3785262" role="oth" change="#role-assignment">Shāh Ismāʻīl of Persia (reigned <date calendar="Hijri-qamari" notBefore="1502" notAfter="1524">907-930</date>)
                        </persName>
                     </note>
                     <note>Composed at the invitation of <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="alt" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/78638870" key="viaf_78638870" role="pat" change="#role-assignment">Shāh Ṭahmāsp (reigned <date calendar="Hijri-qamari" notBefore="1524" notAfter="1576">930-984</date>)
                        </persName>
                     </note>
                     <note>This copy may be unique</note>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>For a more detailed description see Arberry 1939, pages 386-7.</bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                     <note/>
